<|startoftext|>I have stopped at this location for some breakfast sandwiches several times and have enjoyed the food and service. It has a great variety of sandwiches and wraps. I get the pork baja sandwich with spicy mayo or ketchup. You don't get any guacamole, but you get some sweet salsa. The pork is flavorful and comes with a side of fried chicken. Both are very flavorful. It has a nice consistency and they have different toppings available. This location takes credit cards!<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>Came here on a Saturday afternoon with a co-worker and my husband for lunch.  The place was busy and we were first in line at 9:15AM.  We ordered the following:  - the egg taco with chips & salsa. It was $4 so we added a $0.50 tax and got the same amount with chips and salsa and that was pretty good.\n\n- the black bean quesadilla: this would have been a 5th or 6th item to order, but came out to the table with 2 quesadillas and a tortilla. If you're using quesadillas then you definitely want to order it with chips. It came out fairly quickly.\n\n- the black bean burrito was really good. It was flavorful as well and everything looked great. The toppings were generous, like you'd get at most any Mexican restaurant (except maybe El Gordo, which you're probably thinking that's a bit too pricey).\n\nThe burritos are also very good and they do have a wide variety of burritos to choose from. You won't likely get to taste all of them here, but if you do then it won't be bad either.  One that stood out was the avocado y chamacin, but I think it would've been better if it had been cooked in an extra layer of chamacin or had just some avocado thrown in there. The y-chaman could have also been served in a tortilla, so the flavor could've been dialed down a bit.\n\nThe chicken enchiladas were great, and the guacamole was great as well. The flavors here were great and the customer service was on point. I can't wait to try the rest of the menu and I would definitely come back here when I am back in town.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>Very good food and very good service. I would definitely go back.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>I'm not sure why this isn't one of my favourite hotels but I'll take it.  A really nice place to stay and the room was very comfortable for my price.  The price for a room had been set by the night before and I never seen it change! It was quite reasonable even for the big hotel.  The whole time I was in the room there was not a negative vibe. The room I had was quite comfortable and had some extra room, but the bed was rather small so it was more comfortable to have a bit more cushion. Overall I'd go back to this hotel for a really great price.  Definitely one of the top hotels I've stayed at!<|endoftext|>
